│ core problem is an unsound optimization of `and (icmp        │
│ samesign), (icmp samesign)` that fails to correctly model    │
│ `poison` semantics, leading to an incorrect transformation   │
│ that introduces undefined behavior.\n\n### 2. Analyzing      │
│ `opt`'s Log (Unchanged)\nThe log correctly identifies that a │
│ transformation within `visitAnd` is the source of the error, │
│ changing a `false` result to `poison`.\n\n### 3. Root Cause  │
│ Analysis (Corrected)\nThe root cause is in                   │
│ `InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp`. The `visitAnd` function           │
│ identifies an `and` with two `ICmpInst` operands (around     │
│ line 2726) and calls `foldAndOrOfICmps` to simplify it. This │
│ helper function does not handle the three-valued logic       │
│ (`true`/`false`/`poison`) of `samesign` predicates           │
│ correctly, leading it to make invalid assumptions and        │
│ perform an illegal transformation.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit   │
│ Point(s) (Corrected)\nThe fix is to add a guard in           │
│ `visitAnd` to prevent `foldAndOrOfICmps` from being called   │
│ if either of the `icmp` instructions uses the `samesign`     │
│ predicate.\n\nThe edit will be in                            │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp`. I │
│ will modify the `if (LHS && RHS)` check to include a         │
│ bail-out for `samesign`.\n\n```cpp\n// Edit Point 1\n//      │
│ File:                                                        │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp\n//  │
│ Lines: 2728-2730\n// ---\n    if (LHS && RHS) {\n      //    │
│ This fold is not safe with samesign.\n      if               │
│ (LHS->isSameSign() || RHS->isSameSign())\n        return     │
│ nullptr;\n      if (Value *Res = foldAndOrOfICmps(LHS, RHS,  │
│ I, /* IsAnd */ true))\n        return replaceInstUsesWith(I, │
│ Res);\n    }\n// ---\n```\n\n### 5. Conclusion\nThe issue    │
│ stems from an overly aggressive optimization in              │
│ `foldAndOrOfICmps` that is not sound for `samesign`          │
│ comparisons. By adding a guard in the `visitAnd` function to │
│ prevent this optimization from running on `samesign`         │
│ predicates, we can resolve the incorrect transformation      │
│ while preserving the optimization for all other valid        │
│ cases."})                                                    │
