│ This is an interesting bug. The core of the issue lies in an │
│ incorrect optimization within `InstCombine` that doesn't     │
│ properly account for the three-valued logic                  │
│ (`true`/`false`/`poison`) of the `icmp samesign` predicate.  │
│ The `foldAndOrOfICmps` function, which is designed to        │
│ simplify logical `and`/`or` operations on `icmp`             │
│ instructions, makes assumptions that are valid for standard  │
│ predicates but break down with `samesign`.                   │
│                                                              │
│ The reproducer demonstrates a case where `(icmp samesign     │
│ ...) and (icmp samesign ...)` is incorrectly simplified. The │
│ optimizer fails to recognize that a specific input can cause │
│ one of the comparisons to yield `poison` due to differing    │
│ signs, while the overall expression should correctly         │
│ evaluate to `false`. The faulty optimization transforms this │
